 20px 0;">Packy here. Most people think Richard Nixon was a dick because of=
 Watergate. I think Richard Nixon was a dick because he passed the 1970 Con=
trolled Substances Act as part of the War on Drugs and classified psychedel=
ics Schedule I substances. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Schedule I substances are =
considered to have a high potential for abuse, no currently accepted medica=
l use (in the United States), and are unsafe to use even if under supervisi=
on by healthcare professionals. That classification killed research into ps=
ychedelics such as MDMA (added to the list in 1985), psilocybin, and LSD, d=
espite the fact that these drugs don&#8217;t fit the definition of Schedule=
 I substances. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Fortunately, research has picked back =
up in recent years, especially for the treatment of PTSD and treatment-resi=
stant depression. In 2017, the FDA granted &#8220;breakthrough therapy&#822=
1; status to MDMA-assisted therapy as a treatment for PTSD.</p><p style=3D"=
color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20p=
x 0;"><span>This most recent research, from </span><a href=3D"https://subst=
ack.com/redirect/7802098f-6f48-433d-b953-022b23775e0b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Qif=
Q.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, =
64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">MAPS</a><span>, is the second of Phas=
e 3 trials on the impact of MDMA plus talk therapy on PTSD. After one sessi=
on, 9.4% of patients went into remission. After three sessions, </span><str=
ong>46.2% of patients went into remission</strong><span>. Only 13.5% of peo=
ple didn&#8217;t respond &#8212; another 25% no longer met the PTSD diagnos=
tic criteria and another 15.3% had at least a 10 point reduction in severit=
y from baseline. </span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Interestingly, the plac=
ebo group also improved, with 21.4% going into remission after three sessio=
ns with the placebo plus therapy. But MDMA was the clear winner. This </spa=
n><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/15275af7-1684-4904-8257-b85f=
f4384d79?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU=
" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">New Yor=
k Times </a></em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/15275af7-1684-490=
4-8257-b85ff4384d79?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8=
-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underlin=
e;">article</a><span> has more details on the study and the results.</span>=
</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0;">An astonishing 5% of American adults are affected by =
PTSD each year, and sadly, many believe that suicide is the only way out. M=
APS is now planning to submit the results to the FDA as part of its applica=
tion to market MDMA + talk therapy as a treatment for PTSD. If approved, it=
 will provide PTSD sufferers with a real alternative. </p><p style=3D"color=
: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"=
